cs.LG, cs.AI, cs.CV, cs.CL, cs.NE 

The paper proposes a method for disentangling factors of interest in Variational Autoencoder (VAE) using pairwise ordinal comparisons. This falls under the category of unsupervised learning and generative models, which are typically covered in the sub-categories of machine learning (cs.LG), artificial intelligence (cs.AI), computer vision (cs.CV), natural language processing (cs.CL), and neural and evolutionary computing (cs.NE). Given that the paper focuses on disentanglement in VAEs, which is a popular topic in machine learning research, cs.LG is the most likely sub-category. However, the other sub-categories are also relevant as they cover related topics such as image and language processing, which are commonly used in VAE applications.
